加拿大新冠患者之谜：出院两周为何仍称检出阳性？。
The Mystery of the New Crown Patients in Canada: Why did they still claim to be positive two weeks after discharge?
2020-02-16 08:15:55来源： 财新网作者：何京蔚 黄蕙昭责任编辑：任波。
2020-02-16 08: 15: 55 Source: Caixin net author: Wei HuiZhao He Jingwei responsible editor: Ren Bo.
2020年02月16日 08:15。
16 February 2020 08: 15.
来源于。
From sources.
财新网。
Caixin Net.
可以听文章啦！。
Listen to the passage.
根据相关冠状病毒感染特性的研究，感染者临床症状痊愈，但核酸检测依然呈病毒阳性并不罕见，原因则有多重可能；此时是否具传染性尚待进一步研究。
According to the study of coronavirus infection characteristics, the infected person recovered from clinical symptoms, but it is not uncommon for nucleic acid tests to be positive for multiple reasons; the infectivity at this time remains to be further studied.
多伦多市确诊的两例新冠肺炎患者，临床诊断已经痊愈，两人鼻咽拭子检测结果仍为阳性，至今在家隔离，此时距其中的男性住院患者痊愈出院已过去两周。
In Toronto, two cases of nosocomial pneumonia were clinically diagnosed and their nasopharyngeal swab test results were positive and remain isolated at home, two weeks after the male hospitalized patient had recovered and was discharged.
图/视觉中国。
Photo / visual China.
相关报道【财新周刊】显影|新冠时期，5个普通人的隔离日记法国出现亚洲以外首例新冠死亡病例 死者为80岁中国游客埃及确诊1人 为非洲首例新冠肺炎病例解药|不止钟南山指导的团队，多款新冠快检技术冲刺中攻克新冠病毒离不开科研，最新进展有哪些。
NEW WEEK & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45;
【财新网】（实习记者 何京蔚 记者 黄蕙昭）北京时间2月14日，加拿大安大略省卫生厅召开新闻发布会，通报当地新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情。
Feb. 14, 2007, the Ontario Ministry of Health in Canada held a press conference to report on the new coronavirus pneumonia in Canada.
发言人芭芭拉·亚菲(Babara Yaffe)表示，多伦多市确诊的两例新冠肺炎患者，临床诊断已经痊愈，两人鼻咽拭子检测结果仍为阳性，至今在家隔离，此时距其中的男性住院患者痊愈出院已过去两周。
Spokeswoman Babara Yaffe said the two cases diagnosed in Toronto had been clinically diagnosed and their nasopharyngeal swabs were still positive and remained isolated at home, two weeks after their male inpatients had recovered and been discharged.
。
.
收治患者的新宁(Sunnybrook)医院称，该男性患者于当地时间1月23日，因发烧和呼吸道症状前来就医。
The patient's Sunnybrook hospital said the man came to the hospital on January 23, local time with fever and respiratory symptoms.
四日后，安大略省卫生厅确诊其为新冠肺炎。
Four days later, Ontario Ministry of Health confirmed New Crown Pneumonia.
1月31日，新宁医院与当地卫生部门会诊后，患者因恢复良好被允许出院，这也是加拿大首例治愈出院的病例。
On January 31, after a consultation with local health authorities at Xinning Hospital, the patient was released from hospital for good health, the first case to be cured in Canada.
患者的妻子在1月29日被确诊为新冠肺炎，由于症状较轻居家隔离，并未前往医院。
The patient's wife, who was diagnosed with pneumonia on January 29, did not go to the hospital because her symptoms were less severe.
。
.
男性患者出院后，这对夫妇接受了安大略省卫生厅的病原核酸检测，结果均为阳性。
After the male patients were released from hospital, the couple underwent an Ontario Ministry of Health pathogen nucleic acid test, all of which were positive.
。
.
“这些检测样本中残留了一些遗传物质或病毒物质，我们还不知道这意味着什么。
"We don't know what it means to have some genetic material or viral material left in these test samples.
”安大略省卫生厅医学微生物学负责人凡尼莎·艾伦（Vanessa Allen）告诉财新记者，按照规定，为避免出现“假阳性”的情况，第一次检测发现了病毒核酸，那么第二次核酸阳性的检测结果就要由当地卫生厅和加拿大国家微生物实验室共同确认。
Vanessa Allen, director of medical microbiology at Ontario's Department of Health, told Caixin that, as a rule, to avoid "false positives" in which viral nucleic acids are detected in the first test, the second nucleic acid-positive test results are jointly confirmed by the local Department of Health and the Canadian National Microbiology Laboratory.
。
.
一位免疫领域专家向财新记者透露，根据相关冠状病毒感染特性的研究，感染者临床症状痊愈，但核酸检测依然呈病毒阳性，并不罕见。
An expert in the field of immunization told Caixin that it was not uncommon for infected people to recover from clinical symptoms based on research into the coronavirus infection characteristics.
针对该夫妇的情况，安大略省卫生厅发言人大卫·威廉（David Williams）称，这位男性患者年龄50多岁，且身患其他基础性疾病，“这可能削弱他清除体内病毒的能力”。
In the couple's case, Ontario Health Department spokesman David Williams said the man was in his fifties and suffered from other basic illnesses, "which could impair his ability to get rid of viruses from his body."
。
.
问题在于，临床良好而病毒阳性的患者，是否仍然具备传染性？答案尚不明确。
The question is whether patients who are clinically good and HIV-positive are still infectious? The answer is unclear.
凡尼莎·艾伦称，目前“无法确定病毒是死是活”：必须要有足够的阴性对照样本，才能确定当前样本中发现的病毒遗传物质是不是代表了活体病毒的存在，而且这些检测必须至少间隔24小时。
According to Vanessa Allen, it is "impossible to determine whether the virus is dead or alive": a sufficient negative control sample is needed to determine whether the genetic material found in the current sample represents the presence of a live virus, and that these tests must be at least 24 hours apart.
。
.
此外，目前无法排除出院患者二次感染的可能。
In addition, the possibility of secondary infection in patients discharged from hospital cannot be ruled out.
不过，根据中日友好医院肺炎防治专家组组长詹庆元此前的解释，从一般病毒感染规律来看，病毒感染之后都会产生一定的抗体，对人体产生保护作用；有的抗体可能持续时间较短，导致已经痊愈的患者有再感染的风险，但可能性较小。
However, according to Zhan Qingyuan, the head of the pneumonia prevention and treatment group at the Sino-Japanese Friendship Hospital, the virus itself produces antibodies that protect the body from common viral infections. Some antibodies may be short-lived, resulting in a reduced risk of reinfection for those who have recovered.
多位专家表示，目前证据不足以说明病人好转了以后会再得新冠肺炎。
Experts say there is not enough evidence to suggest that patients will get pneumonia again when they get better.
（参见：专家：新冠病毒二次感染非主要问题，当前应聚焦疫情控制）。
(Refer to: Expert: secondary infection is not a major problem. Focus on outbreak control.)
值得注意的是，中加两国出院标准并不统一。
It is worth noting that the discharge standards of China and Canada are not uniform.
按照加拿大所参考的美国疾控中心方案，如已无临床症状，住院患者就可以出院回家自行隔离，期间接受病原核酸检测，以确认是否解除隔离；轻症患者最初也可选择不前往医院，但应当接受严格的医学观察。
According to the United States CDC Program referenced by Canada, hospitalized patients can be discharged from the hospital to isolate themselves without clinical symptoms, where they undergo a pathogen nucleic acid test to confirm whether or not isolation has been lifted, and light patients may initially choose not to go to a hospital, but should undergo rigorous medical observation.
。
.
但根据中国国家卫健委《新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎诊疗方案（试行第五版）》，新冠病毒感染者除临床症状消失外，还必须连续两次呼吸道病原核酸检测阴性(采样间隔至少1天)，才可以判定治愈出院。
But according to the Chinese National Fitness and Health Commission's "Diagnosis and Treatment of Pneumonia due to New Coronavirus Infection (Trial 5th Edition)," two consecutive negative RNA tests (at least one day between samples) must be performed in addition to clinical symptoms before a successful discharge can be determined.
。
.
一位黄石的新冠肺炎“高度疑似”（即，核酸检测呈弱阳性）患者曾向财新记者表示，自己入院隔离约5天后，肺部CT已显示明显好转，无其它临床症状。
A "highly suspected" Yellowstone patient with New Crown Pneumonia (viz., weak nucleic acid test) told Caixin News that after about five days of isolation, pulmonary CT had shown a marked improvement and showed no other clinical symptoms.
而医生在连续两次核酸阴性后，甚至坚持“以防万一”做了第三次核酸检测，才同意他出院。
After two consecutive negative nucleic acids, doctors even insisted on a third nucleic acid test "just in case" before agreeing to his release.
。
.
2月11日，国家医疗专家组成员钟南山院士同广东医疗队武汉前方ICU团队进行远程视频会诊时表示，相关部门对一些已经康复的病人仍然采取了留院隔离的措施，因为他们不想冒风险。
On February 11, Chinese academician Zhong Nan-shan, a member of the National Medical Expert Group, said during a tele-video consultation with the Guangdong Medical Team's forward ICU team in Wuhan that some recovered patients had been placed in isolation because they did not want to take risks.
“他们不知道这些已经康复的病人是否还会再次感染，所以出院率目前看起来并不高。
"They don't know if the patients who have recovered will get reinfection, so the discharge rate doesn't seem high at the moment.
”。
"
可以推测，若该多伦多夫妇检测显示临床症状消失但体内病毒仍具有活性，当地或须重新评估出院标准。
Presumably, if the Toronto couple tests showed clinical symptoms to disappear but the vivo virus was still active, the discharge criteria might have to be re-evaluated locally.
。
.
截至2月14日，加拿大现有确诊新冠肺炎患者7例，其中安大略省3例，不列颠哥伦比亚省4例。
As of February 14, there were seven confirmed cases of New Crown Pneumonia in Canada, three in Ontario and four in British Columbia.
。
.
现下对新型冠状病毒的了解仍旧有限，此前，有研究团队从新冠肺炎患者的粪便样本中发现了活病毒，但专家们指出，目前还没有充分证据证实“粪口传播”。
Knowledge of the new coronavirus is still limited after a team of researchers found live virus in human feces from patients with pneumonia, but experts said there was insufficient evidence of "fecal transmission."
新冠病毒能否通过气溶胶传播，也需要接下来的研究证实或证伪。
Whether the new canopy virus can be transmitted via aerosols also requires subsequent research to confirm or falsify.
随着确诊病例情况的逐渐复杂化，对新型冠状病毒的病理研究亟待进一步开展。
With the increasing complexity of the confirmed case, the pathology of the new coronavirus needs to be further studied.
。
.
